[00:00.00]General Listening Quiz &#8220;Evening Routine&#8221; (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); See Listening Script Back to Easy Quizzes .lesson-links { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 0px 0 0px 0; } .lesson-link { color: #174973; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.2s; } .lesson-link:hover { color: #005a87; text-decoration: underline; } ◄ Previous Activity Next Activity ► .spacedlist li { margin-bottom: 10px; } ul.vocabulary li { margin-bottom: 10px; } /* Add space above nested lists */ .spacedlist li ul, .spacedlist li ol, ul.vocabulary li ul, ul.vocabulary li ol { margin-top: 10px; } .table-container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; overflow-x: auto; } .overview-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; border: 1px solid #666; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); } .overview-table th, .overview-table td { padding: 12px 15px; text-align: center; border: 1px solid #666; } .overview-table th { background: #f0f6fb; font-weight: bold; color: #333; } /* Mobile */ @media (max-width: 600px) { .overview-table { box-shadow: none; border: none; } .overview-table thead { display: none; } .overview-table tr { display: block; margin-bottom: 15px; border: 1px solid #666; } .overview-table td { display: block; text-align: right; padding: 10px 15px; position: relative; border: none; border-top: 1px solid #999; } .overview-table td:first-child { border-top: none; } .overview-table td::before { content: attr(data-label); position: absolute; left: 15px; font-weight: bold; color: #333; text-align: left; } } Level Topic Speakers Length Easy Evening Activities Man &#8211; Woman 01:30 Pre-Listening Exercise What time do you usually eat dinner? Do you prefer cooking at home or eating out in the evening? What do you usually do after dinner? Do you go to bed early, or do you stay up late? Agree or Disagree? Let’s Spark Some Conversation! Do you agree or disagree with these statements. Talk together and share your opinions. Dinner is the most enjoyable meal of the day. People should avoid watching TV in the evening. Cooking at home is always healthier than eating out. Checking the news before bed makes it hard to relax. Everyone should have a regular bedtime. Reading before bed is better than watching TV. Going to sleep late is fine as long as you get enough hours. Eating late at night is unhealthy. Evening routines are more important than morning routines. Technology makes it harder for people to fall asleep. Idioms “call it a day” = stop working or doing something for the evening “After dinner, Mark decided to call it a day and watch TV.” “hit the sack” = go to bed “Lisa brushed her teeth and then hit the sack around 11:30.” Listening Exercise Listen to the recording and answer the questions. ( See transcript ) https://esllab.b-cdn.net/audio/mp3/e_evening_routine.mp3 /* Button styling */ .audio-speed-btn { font-weight: bold; font-size: 16px; color: #000; margin-right: 6px; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s ease; } .audio-speed-btn:hover { background-color: #5dade2; color: #fff; } .audio-speed-btn.active { background-color: #5dade2; color: #fff; } /* 📱 Mobile adjustments */ @media (max-width: 768px) { .audio-speed-btn { font-size: 12px; /* slightly smaller on tablets */ } } @media (max-width: 480px) { .audio-speed-btn { font-size: 12px; /* smaller on phones */ } } document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() { const audio = document.querySelector("audio"); if (!audio) return; // Create wrapper for buttons const wrapper = document.createElement("div"); wrapper.className = "uk-margin-small-top"; // ✅ spacing using Yootheme Pro class wrapper.style.display = "flex"; wrapper.style.alignItems = "center"; // Label const label = document.createElement("span"); label.innerText = "Speed:"; label.style.fontWeight = "bold"; label.style.marginRight = "8px"; wrapper.appendChild(label); // Speed buttons const speeds = [0.75, 0.85, 1, 1.25]; speeds.forEach(speed => { const btn = document.createElement("button"); btn.className = "audio-speed-btn"; btn.innerText = speed + "x"; btn.onclick = () => { audio.playbackRate = speed; wrapper.querySelectorAll(".audio-speed-btn").forEach(b => b.classList.remove("active")); btn.classList.add("active"); }; wrapper.appendChild(btn); }); // Skip back 5s button const skipBtn = document.createElement("button"); skipBtn.className = "audio-speed-btn"; skipBtn.innerText = "⏪ Back 5s"; skipBtn.title = "Go back 5 seconds"; // tooltip for clarity skipBtn.onclick = () => { audio.currentTime = Math.max(0, audio.currentTime - 5); }; wrapper.appendChild(skipBtn); // Insert buttons after audio player audio.insertAdjacentElement("afterend", wrapper); // Set default speed 1x audio.playbackRate = 1; const defaultBtn = Array.from(wrapper.querySelectorAll(".audio-speed-btn")) .find(b => parseFloat(b.innerText) === 1); if (defaultBtn) defaultBtn.classList.add("active"); }); Evening Routine What time does Lisa eat dinner? What did Lisa eat for dinner? Mark usually ________ after dinner. Mark sometimes stays up late if he ________. Great Job! Nice try! Review your answers. medianet_width = "728"; medianet_height = "90"; medianet_crid = "842863434"; medianet_versionId = "3111299"; Vocabulary and Sample Sentences Here are some words that appear in the recording: evening ( noun ) : the time of day between late afternoon and night &#8211; Lisa is glad it&#8217;s evening after her busy day. takeout ( noun ) : food you order from a restaurant to eat at home &#8211; Lisa sometimes orders takeout when she feels too tired to cook. online ( adverb or adjective ) : using the internet or connected to the internet &#8211; Lisa usually watches shows or movies online . &#8211; Sometimes, I watch online movies in the evenings. relax ( verb ) : to rest and become less stressed &#8211; Mark listens to music in the evening to relax . homework ( noun ) : schoolwork that students must do at home &#8211; Mark stays up late when he has a lot of homework . Post-Listening Exercise What is your typical evening routine? Do you think watching TV or using your phone before bed affects your sleep? How? How late is “too late” to go to bed? Do you believe evening routines are more about relaxation or preparation for the next day? If you could improve one thing about your evenings, what would it be? Online Investigation Use the internet (or talk with a classmate) to explore evening routines in three different countries . Answer these questions: What time do people usually eat dinner? What types of foods are common for dinner? Do people watch TV, go out, or spend evenings in other ways? How do people prepare for bed in those cultures (tea, bathing, reading, prayer, etc.)? Keep Learning With Related Language Activities 🎧 Related Listening Activity ✅ Next Level Challenge 📝 Self-Study Guide ⭐ Randall&#8217;s Favorites Disclosure: Randall developed this content through collaboration with AI, combining technological support with professional instructional design. .lesson-links { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; padding: 0px 0 0px 0; } .lesson-link { color: #174973; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; transition: color 0.2s; } .lesson-link:hover { color: #005a87; text-decoration: underline; } ◄ Previous Activity Next Activity ► See Listening Script Back to Easy Quizzes Try More Free Listening at DailyESL.com Follow Randall: (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); Study Guide Academic English Listening Basic English Quizzes Easy Listening Intermediate Listening Difficult Listening English Grammar Lessons Interviews English Idioms English Culture Videos ESL Vocabulary Quizzes medianet_width = "300"; medianet_height = "600"; medianet_crid = "621252724"; medianet_versionId = "3111299"; (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});